contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:08.954 --> 01:13.758
- What are you doing up?
- Can't sleep. You?

01:13.792 --> 01:15.760
Hm...

01:15.794 --> 01:20.565
I remember when you used to crawl
into bed with me when that happened.

01:20.599 --> 01:24.001
Yeah, I thought I'd, uh, spare you tonight.

01:24.036 --> 01:27.738
Hm. Then you'd end up
sprawled out sideways,

01:27.773 --> 01:30.942
your feet next to my head, kicking
me in the face all night long.

01:30.976 --> 01:34.712
See, I remember it as you
headbutting my feet, actually.

01:34.746 --> 01:38.983
Really? Then Mama would viciously
attack your elbows with her ribs?

01:39.017 --> 01:41.719
- Really?
- [laughs]

01:41.753 --> 01:46.824
Yeah. Sorry about that. Sounds terrible.

01:48.994 --> 01:52.830
Eh... it was pretty nice.

01:55.667 --> 01:59.070
Back when that was all it
took to make you feel safe.

02:05.811 --> 02:11.582
- How's it feel?
- About the same.

02:12.818 --> 02:13.784
Still numb?

02:17.990 --> 02:21.659
What if I, um...

02:21.693 --> 02:24.896
... can't ever play again...

02:24.930 --> 02:26.564
... like I used to?

02:28.033 --> 02:29.800
Honey, don't think like that.

02:30.235 --> 02:34.572
You can't think like that, ok?

02:35.974 --> 02:39.644
You just have to keep
trying, keep at it, you know?

02:39.678 --> 02:42.713
Don't you ever give up on
your dream, you hear me?

03:17.649 --> 03:21.719
[theme music plays]

03:21.753 --> 03:24.789
♪ It's not where you come from ♪

03:24.823 --> 03:27.992
♪ It's where you belong ♪

03:28.026 --> 03:30.761
♪ Nothing I would trade ♪

03:30.796 --> 03:33.998
♪ I wouldn't have it any other way ♪

03:34.032 --> 03:39.670
♪ You're surrounded by
love and you're wanted ♪

03:39.705 --> 03:42.974
♪ So never feel alone ♪

03:43.008 --> 03:45.710
♪ You're home with me ♪

03:45.744 --> 03:49.046
♪ Right where you belong ♪

03:52.047 --> 03:56.000
- synced and corrected by chamallow -
- www.addic7ed.com -

04:07.416 --> 04:10.585
- We don't have any oranges?
- Sorry. I think I took the last one.

04:13.455 --> 04:15.623
And the bread? All we have are the ends.

04:15.657 --> 04:17.391
This is like The Hunger Games.

04:17.426 --> 04:19.527
You do know those books aren't
actually about food, right?

04:19.560 --> 04:21.661
Sorry, guys, I'll hit the
market today, I promise.

04:21.697 --> 04:24.432
- Good morning.
- Morning. Are we out of... ?

04:24.466 --> 04:26.834
- Everything!
- Bacon, we've got bacon. Have some bacon. Come on.

04:31.507 --> 04:32.571
I made it last night.

04:32.572 --> 04:35.188
I want everybody home
for family dinner tonight.

04:35.477 --> 04:37.411
- Five p.m. Yes?
- Wrestling won't be done...

04:37.446 --> 04:39.714
- What about dance?
- Do I hear six p.m.? Anybody?

04:39.748 --> 04:41.782
I have work, I was just
gonna eat there with Daphne.

04:42.918 --> 04:45.853
But I will eat here instead.

04:45.888 --> 04:48.890
Um, I'm supposed to go to
the batting cages with Connor.

04:50.526 --> 04:52.693
Batting cages, as in baseball?

04:52.728 --> 04:55.496
Yeah, Connor and his dad go all
the time. And they invited me.

04:55.531 --> 04:56.764
- I think that's great, sweetheart.
- Mm.

04:56.798 --> 04:58.799
I never knew you were a baseball guy.

04:58.834 --> 04:59.819
I haven't really played that much.

04:59.820 --> 05:02.565
But who knows, maybe I'm really good.

05:02.771 --> 05:06.707
- Yeah, maybe.
- Just have fun, baby, that's all that counts.

05:08.443 --> 05:10.611
So, Mom, I was thinking about
what you said last night.

05:10.646 --> 05:12.380
- Uh-huh?
- About not giving up?

05:12.414 --> 05:15.716
- Right.
- And I think I want the surgery.

05:15.751 --> 05:19.420
Try to repair the nerve damage.

05:21.456 --> 05:23.524
Ok. Um...

05:23.559 --> 05:26.727
The doctor said that it's a
difficult and complex procedure.

05:26.762 --> 05:30.498
And if things don't go as hoped,
your hand could actually get worse.

05:30.532 --> 05:33.668
Yeah, I mean, she said
there's a chance of that.

05:33.702 --> 05:37.405
She also said that if the
surgery did cause damage,

05:37.439 --> 05:40.541
that it could... it could
actually be permanent.

05:40.576 --> 05:42.643
[Lena] You've got almost
95 percent function now.

05:42.678 --> 05:44.779
That's better than the doctors even hoped.

05:44.813 --> 05:48.649
But if I'm gonna play piano,
though, I need 100 percent.

05:48.684 --> 05:49.750
So I'd like to give it a shot.

05:58.560 --> 06:00.795
- So we agreed? You're good?
- Yeah. It's the right call.

06:00.829 --> 06:02.563
- Ok.
- Ok.

06:02.598 --> 06:04.565
- I'll let Brandon know.
- Ok.

06:04.600 --> 06:08.703
Oh, and tell him if he wants to
come by, that, you know, I'm here.

06:08.737 --> 06:11.706
- I will.
- Ok. Gotta hit the shower.

06:11.740 --> 06:13.708
- Let yourself out?
- Yeah.

06:15.677 --> 06:17.745
Thanks a lot for letting me
barge in like this. Appreciate it.

06:17.779 --> 06:20.748
- Oh, no worries.
- Ok, uh...

06:20.782 --> 06:22.683
You know, there's something
I wanted to ask you,

06:22.718 --> 06:27.388
something Brandon told me about
the night before he was attacked.

06:27.422 --> 06:29.724
- Um...
- [door closes]

06:30.859 --> 06:35.529
- Mike was drinking?
- Oh. Um...

06:35.564 --> 06:37.565
Yeah. He had a little slip,

06:37.599 --> 06:42.436
but he's been sober ever since,
going to meetings every day.

06:42.471 --> 06:45.406
Oh, that's great. Good for him.

06:45.440 --> 06:46.841
Brandon said that he was in a fight.

06:46.875 --> 06:49.443
Yeah, I guess so.

06:49.478 --> 06:51.646
He blacked out so he didn't
really remember anything.

06:51.680 --> 06:53.848
Oh, gosh...

06:53.882 --> 06:57.418
But there was blood on his hands
when you found him? That's...

06:57.452 --> 07:01.389
A little. He was fine.

07:01.423 --> 07:05.493
- Was it his blood?
- Stef.

07:05.527 --> 07:09.430
If you have questions about Mike's
sobriety, you have to ask him.

07:09.464 --> 07:12.767
Of course. Of course I
should. You're right. Sorry.

07:12.801 --> 07:15.703
Thank you so much for
the coffee. Appreciate it.

07:25.781 --> 07:30.484
All right, Jude, just keep
your eye on the ball, buddy.

07:35.524 --> 07:40.428
[laughs] Takes a little getting
used to. Just hang in there, kid.

07:42.531 --> 07:44.340
- [bat clatters]
- Um, you might wanna

07:44.341 --> 07:45.998
hang on to the bat a little tighter too.

07:46.135 --> 07:48.602
Here, grab another one, all right?
Hey, Connor, let's go, come on.

07:48.637 --> 07:50.638
Throw a token in there, let's
see what you got. Come on, buddy.

07:52.841 --> 07:54.442
What'd we talk about this year?

07:54.476 --> 07:55.876
- Balance and torque.
- That's right, come on.

07:55.911 --> 07:57.745
Let's go! See what you got.

08:00.482 --> 08:03.751
Hey, your head's moving all over the
place, like this. You're all over.

08:05.787 --> 08:09.490
Connor, pivot the back
foot. Pivot like this. Pivot.

08:10.659 --> 08:11.792
That's better.

08:13.829 --> 08:15.796
Hey, way to go. Nice hit. Good job.

08:15.831 --> 08:19.533
Look, that front foot's gotta
land in the same place every time.

08:19.568 --> 08:22.536
- It slipped.
- No excuses! Come on!

08:22.571 --> 08:27.708
Hey, what's the matter with you? Your
focus is all over the place today.

08:27.743 --> 08:32.379
- [slurping]
- Need a refill? A soda?

08:32.414 --> 08:35.750
- Uh, it's a vanilla shake.
- Oh, yeah. We don't do refills on shakes.

08:35.784 --> 08:39.653
- Yeah. I figured.
- Yeah, vanilla's my favorite.

08:39.688 --> 08:41.655
It has to be really good vanilla, though.

08:41.690 --> 08:44.725
You should, um, check out
the place down the street,

08:44.760 --> 08:48.395
in the mini-mall on
Olamar. Best shakes in town.

08:48.430 --> 08:51.432
[chuckles]

08:51.466 --> 08:54.602
Do you work every day after
school? That's gotta be tough.

08:54.636 --> 08:55.890
Um, no, just three days.

08:55.891 --> 08:57.667
My moms don't want me to
work any more than that.

08:57.672 --> 09:00.574
- Moms?
- Yeah.

09:00.609 --> 09:04.378
- Cool.
- It is.

09:05.514 --> 09:06.514
[clears throat]

09:06.548 --> 09:08.482
Oh, don't worry, I'll grab that.

09:08.517 --> 09:11.585
Oh, thanks. See you soon.

09:11.620 --> 09:15.523
Oh... down the street, I'm telling you.

09:20.529 --> 09:24.565
- You're really good.
- Not good enough.

09:24.599 --> 09:26.700
I thought you did great,
way better than me.

09:26.735 --> 09:28.836
I'm supposed to be good at this.

09:38.513 --> 09:39.713
- Damn!
- What?

09:39.748 --> 09:42.483
- Someone left us a hundred-dollar tip!
- What?

09:42.517 --> 09:45.686
- A hundred dollars, yo!
- Oh, my God! Who do you think it was?

09:45.720 --> 09:48.756
I don't know. Vanilla milkshake?
He sure was chatting you up.

09:48.790 --> 09:51.525
- Please.
- Come on, girl. You know he likes you.

09:51.560 --> 09:53.861
- [laughs] Shut up.
- He wants some of that.

09:53.895 --> 09:56.597
- Daphne!
- If he keeps giving us hundred dollars bills,

09:56.631 --> 09:59.733
- he can have all the vanilla milkshake he want!
- Ow!

09:59.968 --> 10:03.537
I just don't understand why
we have to do any of this.

10:03.572 --> 10:05.773
Well, if you want him to
sign off, these are his terms.

10:05.807 --> 10:08.776
Yes, but it makes no sense. It's not
like she's asking him for anything.

10:12.480 --> 10:13.714
Sit down, love.

10:20.589 --> 10:23.824
So, Callie, we heard back
from Robert Quinn's lawyer.

10:23.859 --> 10:28.662
- Ok.
- And he won't sign anything until there's a DNA test,

10:28.697 --> 10:31.765
to prove that you're his daughter. So...

10:38.506 --> 10:39.874
[scoffs]

10:42.158 --> 10:44.495
I seriously can't handle sharing
the gym with the wrestlers anymore.

10:45.002 --> 10:48.170
- The gym smells like feet.
- Well, that's appetizing.

10:48.205 --> 10:51.207
And all the boys ever
do is stare at us. Pervs.

10:51.275 --> 10:52.430
Well, it's not awesome for me either,

10:52.431 --> 10:54.666
hearing guys talk about
how hot my sister is.

10:55.145 --> 10:58.147
- Which guys?
- Besides, I see the dance team checking us out too.

10:58.181 --> 11:00.783
That Hayley girl, can't
take her eyes off me.

11:00.817 --> 11:03.853
Oh, yeah? Hayley, the one with
the college boyfriend Hayley?

11:03.887 --> 11:04.800
She dates boys in college?

11:04.801 --> 11:06.980
None of the girls on the dance
team date boys in high school.

11:07.157 --> 11:09.992
- Oh. We'll see about that.
- Better not let Emma hear you.

11:10.027 --> 11:13.162
- Please, I can handle Emma.
- [laughter]

11:13.196 --> 11:13.792
What?

11:13.793 --> 11:16.161
I pretty sure no one handles Emma but Emma.

11:16.867 --> 11:20.136
Hey, Brandon! We'd like
to eat, sometime this year!

11:20.170 --> 11:23.005
Jude, how did the batting cages go?

11:23.040 --> 11:26.776
Do we need to call the Padres, see if
they need another big hit in their lineup?

11:26.810 --> 11:27.977
- Huh?
- I don't think so.

11:28.011 --> 11:32.181
Oh, come on! Planning my retirement.

11:32.215 --> 11:35.751
- Bread me.
- Oh! Guys!

11:35.786 --> 11:39.221
So we, uh, make an appointment
yet for the hand surgeon?

11:40.924 --> 11:44.827
- Uh, no.
- Why not?

11:44.861 --> 11:46.862
Um...

11:46.897 --> 11:49.832
Well, I talked it all
over with your father.

11:49.866 --> 11:54.770
Is this about money or something? Isn't
that what the settlement from Vico is for?

11:54.805 --> 11:58.207
- Fix my freaking hand?
- No, Brandon, it's not about money.

11:59.776 --> 12:01.043
We just, um...

12:02.979 --> 12:05.815
we just feel that it's a
little too risky, Brandon.

12:05.849 --> 12:09.151
And, uh... your father and I are saying no.

12:13.190 --> 12:16.025
I don't get this.

12:16.059 --> 12:19.028
It's my hand, my money, my life.

12:19.062 --> 12:22.131
And I wanna play piano
again. Like, really play.

12:22.165 --> 12:25.735
Why is this so hard to
understand? I want the surgery.

12:25.769 --> 12:28.804
Brandon, we are eating dinner.
Can we please discuss this later?

12:28.839 --> 12:31.040
Yeah, well, I'm not hungry.

12:39.182 --> 12:42.885
- So you talked to Mike?
- This afternoon.

12:42.919 --> 12:44.787
Oh.

12:44.821 --> 12:48.891
And you just... decided?

12:50.961 --> 12:52.194
[Jesus] Shouldn't it be Brandon's decision?

12:52.229 --> 12:53.863
He's the one who got his ass kicked.

12:53.897 --> 12:57.032
I wouldn't put it that way,
but that's a good point.

12:57.067 --> 13:00.903
What if it doesn't work? I mean, what
if he can't use his fingers at all?

13:00.937 --> 13:03.005
Look, Mike and I talked
through all of this.

13:03.039 --> 13:07.710
And you made your decision. Got it.

13:14.951 --> 13:16.152
[knock on door]

13:18.155 --> 13:20.122
Hey.

13:20.157 --> 13:23.959
Nice coat rack.

13:23.994 --> 13:26.729
Yeah, well, might as
well use it for something.

13:26.763 --> 13:29.064
Brandon.

13:29.099 --> 13:31.200
I mean, you can still play, right?

13:31.234 --> 13:32.968
Not classical. Not the way I did.

13:33.003 --> 13:35.938
OK, so all music is dead to you then?

13:35.972 --> 13:38.908
- No, but...
- Well, it sounds like that's what you're risking,

13:38.942 --> 13:41.877
- if you have this surgery.
- Ok.

13:41.912 --> 13:45.147
Look, I had a future.

13:45.182 --> 13:47.049
That's not something you just throw away.

13:47.083 --> 13:49.118
But what if you're not throwing it away?

13:49.152 --> 13:52.054
What if it's just... a different future?

13:52.088 --> 13:54.089
What if it doesn't have
to be that way, though?

13:54.124 --> 13:56.826
I mean, why is everyone focusing
on the worst-case scenario?

13:56.860 --> 14:00.796
Ok, yeah, I'm sorry. I hear you. It's...

14:00.831 --> 14:03.966
I hate it when people assume the worst.

14:04.000 --> 14:07.903
- Like your birth dad?
- Yeah, like him.

14:07.938 --> 14:13.075
I guess he owns, like, this
big company or something.

14:13.109 --> 14:16.879
So he is making me take this DNA test

14:16.913 --> 14:20.015
and... and sign this agreement

14:20.050 --> 14:23.052
that says that I'll never sue him. [Laughs]

14:23.086 --> 14:26.822
- That's crazy.
- Like I want his money?

14:26.857 --> 14:30.125
Just sign the papers, and
then sail off on your yacht

14:30.160 --> 14:34.864
and I promise I will never
think of you ever again.

14:34.898 --> 14:37.867
- And I have to see him.
- Why?

14:37.901 --> 14:40.970
'Cause we both have to
be there at the test,

14:41.004 --> 14:44.940
to make sure that nothing
gets switched or whatever.

14:44.975 --> 14:47.877
I know you didn't want to
know anything about him.

14:47.911 --> 14:50.746
Guess I don't have a choice.

14:55.151 --> 14:57.086
Some people do.

14:57.120 --> 14:58.988
Just think about it.

14:59.022 --> 15:01.090
[soft rock plays]

15:04.728 --> 15:07.830
♪ On the other side ♪

15:11.902 --> 15:15.037
I'm really busy, Timothy.
What is it you need?

15:15.071 --> 15:18.841
I, um, wanted to let you
know that I've been asked

15:18.875 --> 15:21.744
to represent the teachers on the
search committee for the new principal.

15:21.778 --> 15:25.814
I know that you have, um, thrown
your hat in the ring, and...

15:25.849 --> 15:27.850
And you should recuse yourself.

15:27.884 --> 15:31.153
What I was going to say was I plan on being

15:31.187 --> 15:35.124
completely professional and keeping
any personal feelings out of it.

15:35.158 --> 15:38.994
- And I hope you will, too.
- So I'm just supposed to trust you on this?

15:39.029 --> 15:41.764
After you gave me your word you
would sign the donor contract,

15:41.798 --> 15:44.733
and then suddenly
decided that you couldn't?

15:46.836 --> 15:48.137
Yeah.

16:09.192 --> 16:10.859
My client will be here any minute.

16:10.894 --> 16:12.895
And my client was pulled
from school for this.

16:22.072 --> 16:26.075
I apologize, Mr. Quinn's been held
up. He won't be able to make it.

16:30.046 --> 16:32.948
Will it be sufficient if you tell Mr.
Quinn everything was done by the book?

16:32.983 --> 16:34.116
Absolutely.

16:41.224 --> 16:43.792
He no-showed? Are you kidding?

16:45.762 --> 16:48.797
What a jerk. He makes you jump
through all these dumb hoops,

16:48.832 --> 16:50.032
the least he could do is show up.

16:50.066 --> 16:53.736
I didn't think I would care.

16:53.770 --> 16:56.205
You know, I had a plan.

16:56.239 --> 16:57.890
I wasn't even gonna look at him.

16:57.914 --> 17:01.650
And when I realized he
wasn't coming at all,

17:01.718 --> 17:05.788
I just got this awful feeling
in the pit of my stomach.

17:08.023 --> 17:10.059
He doesn't even want to see me.

17:11.902 --> 17:14.936
Ugh! I just hate that he
can make me feel like that.

17:16.673 --> 17:19.709
I know. That's the worst.

17:20.743 --> 17:22.435
At least when my birth mom bails

17:22.436 --> 17:24.950
I can tell myself it's 'cause
she's a drug addict, right?

17:24.954 --> 17:27.049
[chuckles] Jealous.

17:27.083 --> 17:28.951
Don't hate.

17:28.985 --> 17:31.787
[laughs]

17:35.892 --> 17:38.994
I did kinda want to see him, though.

17:39.029 --> 17:41.797
Just once.

17:41.831 --> 17:43.866
Just to know.

17:55.586 --> 17:57.487
[knocking]

17:57.521 --> 17:59.556
Hey, uh, do you have any plans tonight?

17:59.590 --> 18:03.693
Um... no, why? Why do you care?

18:03.761 --> 18:07.724
Are you so shallow that you're afraid
your social status will be diminished

18:07.759 --> 18:09.760
by a big brother who doesn't

18:09.794 --> 18:11.695
- Yes.
- [both laugh]

18:11.729 --> 18:15.532
No, but really, Jesus and Emma
are going to some all-ages show

18:15.567 --> 18:18.535
tonight at the Groundspace to see
this band that Emma's friend is in.

18:18.570 --> 18:20.771
Now, Callie wants to come, but
because Wyatt's out of town,

18:20.805 --> 18:23.407
I'm going with her so she
doesn't feel like a third wheel.

18:23.441 --> 18:26.577
- So why do you need me?
- We need a ride.

18:26.611 --> 18:29.746
[laughs] I feel so loved.

18:29.781 --> 18:33.650
Um... I don't know, why
don't you ride with Emma?

18:33.685 --> 18:36.687
We're trying not to be third
and fourth wheels, remember?

18:36.721 --> 18:40.524
- You have to come.
- To listen to some high school garage band?

18:40.558 --> 18:43.427
- Sounds like torture.
- Hey, at least you don't need a fake ID to get in.

18:43.461 --> 18:46.530
- Too soon.
- Come on.

18:54.539 --> 18:56.773
- So?
- Girl, please.

18:56.808 --> 19:00.611
No one says no to Miss Thing. He's in.

19:00.645 --> 19:02.446
[laughs]

19:02.480 --> 19:05.649
- [electronic dance music plays]
- [indistinct chatter]

19:13.424 --> 19:14.825
This better not suck.

19:17.495 --> 19:19.796
- Pull these two tables together.
- Ok.

19:21.833 --> 19:23.767
- Emma!
- Hey!

19:23.835 --> 19:26.637
- You brought a posse. Nice.
- Yeah.

19:26.671 --> 19:28.605
- Hey, man.
- Hey, man. This is your band?

19:28.640 --> 19:31.642
Yeah. It's me, Jasper and my cousin Lou.

19:31.676 --> 19:36.513
Not exactly Arcade Fire,
but we can play a little.

19:36.547 --> 19:39.816
- Hey, you doing all right?
- Oh, yeah. I'm ok.

19:39.851 --> 19:42.819
It's not quite where I
want it to be, but hopefully

19:42.854 --> 19:45.722
one more surgery and I
should be back to top form.

19:45.757 --> 19:48.525
That's great to hear. We're on soon.

19:48.559 --> 19:51.495
Um, Lou just pulled up. Punctual as always.

19:51.529 --> 19:52.663
[boy] A little help, here!

19:52.697 --> 19:55.532
And that's the end of my 20-second break.

19:55.566 --> 19:57.634
Good luck, man.

19:58.870 --> 20:00.704
So, Emma, what kind of music do they play?

20:00.738 --> 20:04.675
It's like an '80s pop vibe
mixed with a little Black Keys.

20:04.709 --> 20:08.578
Cool. This is gonna be painful.

20:08.613 --> 20:10.847
Be nice.

20:10.882 --> 20:14.551
So, Emma, how do you know Mat? [Laughs]

20:14.585 --> 20:17.721
I think what she's trying to ask
is, does he have a girlfriend?

20:17.755 --> 20:19.656
That's definitely what she's trying to ask.

20:19.691 --> 20:20.857
That's not what I was trying to ask.

20:20.892 --> 20:22.726
Do you guys want me to ask? Hey, Mat!

20:22.760 --> 20:25.495
No! That is not what I was asking.

20:25.530 --> 20:27.798
- He's single.
- [applause]

20:32.537 --> 20:35.806
[cheering]

20:37.542 --> 20:39.509
- Lou?
- Yeah. Lucy.

20:39.544 --> 20:42.446
[playing rock music]

20:43.614 --> 20:45.682
We're Someone's Little Sister.

20:45.717 --> 20:47.851
You know the old saying:

20:47.885 --> 20:50.554
yesterday's history, tomorrow's a mystery.

20:50.588 --> 20:54.624
So tonight? We rock your faces off.

20:54.659 --> 20:56.426
[cheering]

20:56.461 --> 20:58.428
♪ I ♪

20:58.463 --> 21:02.399
♪ I don't wanna waste your time ♪

21:02.433 --> 21:05.869
♪ And I don't need you wasting mine ♪

21:05.903 --> 21:08.605
♪ So leave it on the front lawn ♪

21:08.639 --> 21:10.540
Not so painful now, is it?

21:12.477 --> 21:14.411
♪ Drive ♪

21:14.445 --> 21:17.848
♪ Pull back the arrow ♪
♪ Let it fly ♪

21:17.882 --> 21:21.818
♪ We can risk it all tonight ♪

21:21.853 --> 21:24.554
♪ Tomorrow's never gone ♪

21:27.892 --> 21:31.862
♪ Take it, leave it ♪
♪ Show me every secret ♪

21:31.896 --> 21:35.899
♪ Crash on me like before ♪
♪ A little more ♪

21:35.933 --> 21:40.537
♪ Save it, waste it ♪
♪ Long as you can taste it ♪

21:40.571 --> 21:44.474
♪ I'm salt water and
you're the ocean floor ♪

21:44.509 --> 21:47.778
♪ Oh, oh, oh ♪

21:47.812 --> 21:52.582
♪ Oh, oh I waited for you so long ♪

21:52.617 --> 21:56.453
♪ Oh, oh, oh... ♪

21:57.722 --> 21:59.689
You're really burning
the midnight oil, huh?

21:59.724 --> 22:01.491
I got to.

22:01.526 --> 22:04.594
I'm doing the work of two people
until they can hire someone else.

22:04.629 --> 22:06.191
Speaking of which,

22:06.192 --> 22:09.137
guess who's on the search
committee for the new principal?

22:09.534 --> 22:12.536
- Who?
- Timothy.

22:12.570 --> 22:14.771
[laughs]

22:14.806 --> 22:18.408
That seems complicated, doesn't it?

22:18.910 --> 22:21.645
Listen, I know that...

22:21.679 --> 22:23.880
... we could use the money, but, um,

22:23.915 --> 22:25.682
do you really want to be principal?

22:25.716 --> 22:30.821
It seems like it's a lot of work,
and you are pregnant. You know?

22:30.855 --> 22:34.424
Is it really the right
time for this, right now?

22:34.458 --> 22:37.494
No, you're right, it's a terrible time.

22:37.528 --> 22:40.764
But jobs like this don't
come along very often,

22:40.798 --> 22:43.834
especially ones where
I have the inside track.

22:43.868 --> 22:46.636
So yeah, I want it.

22:46.671 --> 22:50.907
And I don't want Timothy to ruin it for me.

22:50.942 --> 22:53.810
- [knocking on door]
- I got it.

22:57.648 --> 23:00.383
- Hey.
- Hey, come on in.

23:04.622 --> 23:06.456
- Hey, Mike.
- Hi.

23:06.490 --> 23:06.975
What's up?

23:07.762 --> 23:11.085
Uh, just work stuff. Can
I talk to you for a sec?

23:11.495 --> 23:14.531
I've got some "work
stuff" of my own to finish.

23:18.903 --> 23:21.738
Are you building a case to
keep Brandon away from me?

23:23.474 --> 23:24.541
No. What are you... ?

23:24.575 --> 23:26.409
Then why are you pumping
Dani for information?

23:26.444 --> 23:28.712
You know I fell off the wagon,
why not just come to me, Stef?

23:28.746 --> 23:32.449
I wasn't pumping Dani for...

23:32.483 --> 23:34.784
You didn't just drink,
Mike, you got into a fight.

23:34.819 --> 23:38.722
- You had blood on your hands.
- So what?

23:38.756 --> 23:40.891
You afraid I'm gonna
hurt Brandon or something?

23:40.925 --> 23:43.660
No, Mike, I'm worried about you.

23:43.694 --> 23:46.796
I'm fine. Ok?

23:46.831 --> 23:50.533
- I'm getting it together.
- Where'd the blood come from?

23:50.568 --> 23:52.702
[sighs]

23:52.737 --> 23:54.804
It's stupid. I got into a fight.

23:54.839 --> 23:57.474
At the bar.

23:57.508 --> 24:00.510
Some guy was bothering the waitress, and...

24:00.544 --> 24:03.647
[sighs] I must have broke his nose.

24:03.681 --> 24:07.450
It was bleeding like crazy.

24:07.485 --> 24:08.852
So you did...

24:08.886 --> 24:10.620
So you didn't see Ana that night?

24:10.655 --> 24:12.422
Is that what this is about?

24:14.825 --> 24:16.459
You think it was her blood?

24:16.494 --> 24:18.595
You were so mad at her, Mike.

24:18.629 --> 24:21.431
Which is why I stayed away,
just like we talked about.

24:21.465 --> 24:23.700
Yeah, you didn't talk to her?
You didn't see her at all?

24:23.734 --> 24:26.670
You didn't try and scare her off
so she wouldn't turn Brandon in... ?

24:26.704 --> 24:29.606
Stef, I swear. I did not talk to Ana,

24:29.640 --> 24:32.442
I certainly didn't lay a hand on her.

24:35.780 --> 24:38.548
Ok. Sorry.

24:42.453 --> 24:43.753
Ok.

24:59.314 --> 25:00.706
Step together.

25:00.707 --> 25:02.480
*** together.

25:02.491 --> 25:08.189
Right, left, and turn! And pose.

25:08.223 --> 25:10.291
I know what you're doing.

25:10.325 --> 25:13.394
What? Hanging out with
my brothers and sisters?

25:13.428 --> 25:17.365
Listening to a little live music?

25:17.399 --> 25:20.568
Look, I think it's nice
and all, but I don't...

25:20.602 --> 25:23.237
Where were those dance moves
when we were up there playing?

25:23.272 --> 25:26.474
- Great show.
- You were awesome!

25:26.508 --> 25:31.479
It was amazing, really. But we have to go.

25:31.513 --> 25:34.248
- We do?
- [imitates whip snapping]

25:34.283 --> 25:36.484
- We do.
- [laughs]

25:36.518 --> 25:38.553
Good job, man.

25:38.587 --> 25:41.589
- What'd you think?
- It was really good.

25:41.623 --> 25:42.943
Come on, you're a musician.

25:42.944 --> 25:44.266
You actually know what
you're talking about.

25:44.560 --> 25:47.428
- Bring it.
- Uh... ok.

25:47.462 --> 25:50.264
Um, your energy was really good.

25:50.299 --> 25:53.267
The songs are good, but, um, I don't know.

25:53.302 --> 25:54.940
I don't think they were being

25:54.941 --> 25:58.411
articulated as well as
they could be, I guess.

25:58.423 --> 26:00.641
I know we're not as tight
as middle school honors band.

26:00.676 --> 26:03.244
You guys used to play together?

26:03.278 --> 26:03.956
Yeah, in seventh grade.

26:03.957 --> 26:07.256
Well, then, you know that Brandon
is a seriously great pianist.

26:08.217 --> 26:12.286
Like, seriously great. Like, even when
I'm so sick of hearing him practice

26:12.321 --> 26:14.622
the same thing over and over again,

26:14.656 --> 26:17.658
that I think if I hear it one more
time I might puncture my own eardrum,

26:17.693 --> 26:21.229
I can step back and recognize
that it's actually pretty amazing.

26:21.263 --> 26:25.233
- Oh, I remember. He's super good.
- He writes, too.

26:25.267 --> 26:27.401
We could use your help
with something, actually.

26:27.436 --> 26:29.570
- No, I don't think...
- Tightening up the sound,

26:29.605 --> 26:31.539
maybe get a few of the songs charted.

26:31.573 --> 26:35.443
So, what, we play the same
stale version every time?

26:35.477 --> 26:37.411
Well, that's only how it starts.

26:37.446 --> 26:40.414
Once you know it, you
can really play around.

26:40.449 --> 26:42.683
Unless you guys like the
fact that you most of the time

26:42.718 --> 26:45.286
sound like you're rehearsing, basically.

26:45.320 --> 26:48.656
[scoffs] You're welcome not to attend
our shows, if you don't like what we do.

26:48.690 --> 26:52.493
No, he didn't mean, um...
no, he's a musician too.

26:52.527 --> 26:53.213
Classical.

26:53.214 --> 26:55.431
Well, maybe you're just
a little too buttoned-up

26:55.564 --> 26:57.231
to get what we're about.

26:59.434 --> 27:03.337
- Wow. She's...
- Intense. Yeah. And I've got, like, 30 seconds

27:03.372 --> 27:05.606
to follow her before
she quits the band again.

27:05.641 --> 27:07.575
But dude, you got to
come jam with us sometime.

27:07.609 --> 27:11.178
I don't think it's my thing. And
it's definitely not her thing.

27:11.213 --> 27:14.348
Just think about it. We could
probably use a little buttoning-up.

27:26.561 --> 27:29.397
- What is it?
- We're in a car.

27:29.431 --> 27:30.631
So?

27:33.268 --> 27:34.702
So, like, our first time
shouldn't be in a car.

27:34.736 --> 27:37.638
Don't worry about me.

27:37.673 --> 27:40.574
I don't need the whole candles
and roses thing if you don't.

27:42.244 --> 27:44.478
- I don't.
- Great.

27:44.513 --> 27:48.582
So, come here and kiss me.

27:53.288 --> 27:56.590
- Could you... less tongue?
- Sure, sure.

27:59.294 --> 28:00.628
Slower.

28:03.498 --> 28:04.465
Ok, switch.

28:09.338 --> 28:11.339
- Kiss my neck.
- You know what?

28:11.373 --> 28:13.307
It's almost time for my curfew.

28:13.342 --> 28:17.178
We better... I better get home. Ok?

28:47.309 --> 28:50.444
[rock music plays on computer]

28:52.514 --> 28:54.582
♪ I ♪

28:54.616 --> 28:58.452
♪ I don't wanna waste your time ♪

28:58.487 --> 29:02.456
♪ And I don't need you wasting mine ♪

29:02.491 --> 29:06.360
♪ So leave it on the front lawn ♪

29:08.563 --> 29:10.431
♪ Drive ♪

29:10.465 --> 29:14.468
♪ Pull back the arrow ♪
♪ Let it fly ♪

29:14.503 --> 29:17.335
♪ We can risk it all tonight ♪

29:17.339 --> 29:18.539
That's really nice. Who is that?

29:18.573 --> 29:23.144
Just some band some kids at school started.

29:23.178 --> 29:26.080
I miss hearing music
pouring from your room.

29:26.114 --> 29:28.215
It's always been one of my favorite things,

29:28.250 --> 29:32.186
even when you were little,
and you weren't very good.

29:32.220 --> 29:33.454
[laughs]

29:33.488 --> 29:36.290
Yeah, well...

29:43.165 --> 29:46.334
You know, for what it's worth,

29:46.368 --> 29:49.470
I think Mom and your dad
are wrong on this one.

29:49.504 --> 29:53.174
I think... .

29:53.208 --> 29:57.478
I think if you want the
operation, it's your hand.

29:57.512 --> 30:00.581
The only one who knows how it feels is you.

30:14.196 --> 30:18.132
Did I really just hear you tell our son
that you think he should get the surgery?

30:35.197 --> 30:37.633
_

30:54.138 --> 30:55.667
This is not what we do, Lena.

30:55.668 --> 30:57.894
What happened to "unified front"?

30:58.414 --> 31:02.385
- I, honestly, I disagree.
- Fine, but you do not go undermining me with our son.

31:02.396 --> 31:04.197
- Our son?
- Yes.

31:04.231 --> 31:06.165
- Or your son?
- [sighs]

31:06.200 --> 31:09.168
Look, Brandon is 16.
He's old enough to know

31:09.203 --> 31:11.204
that we don't always agree on everything.

31:11.238 --> 31:14.307
And I wanted him to know that if he still
believes in this dream, then so do I.

31:14.341 --> 31:17.543
It's not a dream, Lena, it is a fantasy.

31:17.578 --> 31:20.446
Do you really want to see
Brandon devastated again?

31:20.481 --> 31:23.382
We can't protect our
kids from disappointment.

31:23.417 --> 31:26.652
And if it happens, and I'm not entirely
convinced that it will in this situation,

31:26.687 --> 31:28.454
then we help him, we
help him to learn from it.

31:28.489 --> 31:30.490
Well, you have fun with that,

31:30.524 --> 31:33.426
because after all of the disappointments
he's had over the last few months,

31:33.460 --> 31:37.230
I am sick and tired of
teaching him that lesson.

31:49.510 --> 31:52.211
[school bell rings]

31:55.182 --> 31:58.384
Hey. So guess what? Moms just
bought me Dawn of Armageddon 4.

31:58.418 --> 32:01.387
Haven't even played it yet. We
can open it when you come over.

32:04.224 --> 32:05.391
I can't spend the night tonight.

32:05.425 --> 32:09.262
Oh, ok. What about Saturday?

32:10.531 --> 32:15.334
I kinda can't sleep over
at your house... ever.

32:17.504 --> 32:19.639
What?

32:19.673 --> 32:23.376
It's my dad, ok? He won't let me.

32:23.410 --> 32:25.444
Why?

32:25.479 --> 32:28.514
I...

32:28.549 --> 32:32.385
It's ok, just... tell me.

32:34.621 --> 32:37.590
I know it's not true, but my
dad won't let me sleep over

32:37.624 --> 32:39.292
at your house because he thinks you're gay.

32:39.326 --> 32:42.528
I know you're not.

32:42.563 --> 32:47.333
I just... I have to do what he says.

32:47.367 --> 32:48.467
I'm sorry.

32:50.604 --> 32:52.471
What if I was gay?

32:55.175 --> 32:56.209
What do you mean?

32:56.243 --> 32:59.278
Would you not want to
sleep over at my house

32:59.313 --> 33:00.613
if I really was gay?

33:13.327 --> 33:14.594
Hey.

33:14.628 --> 33:18.331
So... don't worry about last night.

33:18.365 --> 33:21.534
It was almost curfew, and
there was a lot of pressure.

33:21.568 --> 33:23.469
Yeah.

33:23.503 --> 33:27.473
But you still want to... right?

33:27.507 --> 33:30.209
Of course.

33:30.244 --> 33:34.247
Um, Saturday night, we'll
do it the right way, ok?

33:34.281 --> 33:36.616
Yeah, I'd like that.

33:38.619 --> 33:40.253
I got it all planned out.

33:40.287 --> 33:43.522
We can go to a really
nice dinner. Totally on me.

33:43.557 --> 33:45.524
And then afterwards, maybe
we can go to the beach.

33:45.559 --> 33:49.662
- The beach?
- Yeah. What's wrong with the beach?

33:49.696 --> 33:52.231
Have you ever had sex on the beach?

33:52.266 --> 33:55.268
I know it's supposed to
be all romantic and stuff,

33:55.302 --> 33:58.504
but there's sand everywhere,

33:58.538 --> 34:02.241
in all your business, and bugs. It's...

34:02.276 --> 34:05.478
It's pretty terrible.

34:05.512 --> 34:09.282
- Ok.
- What?

34:09.315 --> 34:15.154
Nothing. It's just, you're so bossy
sometimes, it's kind of a turn-off.

34:15.188 --> 34:19.225
Bossy? Wow.

34:19.259 --> 34:21.627
Well, I only said that because...

34:21.661 --> 34:23.362
No, that's cool, you know.

34:23.397 --> 34:27.400
I'll just, like, turn my brain
off whenever we're together.

34:27.434 --> 34:28.655
- That's not what I meant.
- So what?

34:28.656 --> 34:30.806
Did I, like, trick you
into this or something?

34:30.813 --> 34:33.239
Did I pretend to be
someone else that you... ?

34:33.273 --> 34:36.409
No. I mean, I like how independent you are.

34:36.476 --> 34:39.178
I just feel like sometimes it's
kinda like you're dating yourself.

34:39.212 --> 34:40.612
Like it doesn't even matter
whether I'm here or not.

34:40.647 --> 34:44.317
Well, congrats. It doesn't anymore.

34:45.418 --> 34:47.320
Emma. Emma!

34:53.226 --> 34:56.228
- Your secret admirer's outside.
- [change rattling]

34:56.263 --> 34:57.530
It's all about the Benjamins, baby.

35:04.638 --> 35:08.174
Just what do you think $100 is
gonna buy you? 'Cause you know what?

35:08.208 --> 35:09.320
I don't want your guilt money.

35:09.321 --> 35:11.300
Yeah, I know who you
are. You're Robert Quinn.

35:13.246 --> 35:15.414
I Googled you, when you didn't show.

35:15.449 --> 35:17.416
Ok, look.

35:17.451 --> 35:18.432
I'm sorry.

35:18.433 --> 35:21.907
I took your DNA test. What
else do you want from me?

35:22.322 --> 35:24.323
Five minutes.

35:31.603 --> 35:34.472
So you've been what? Stalking me?

35:34.506 --> 35:37.875
I just wanted to see you.

35:37.910 --> 35:40.745
If I wanted the best vanilla shakes, I
would have gone down the street, right?

35:42.614 --> 35:44.682
[clears throat] I'm sorry...

35:46.719 --> 35:51.622
Look, you should know that I didn't
want to put you through that test. Ok?

35:51.690 --> 35:53.725
It's my family's lawyers,
they insisted on it.

35:53.759 --> 35:55.660
I don't want your money, ok?

35:55.694 --> 35:58.596
I want your signature on a piece of paper.

35:58.630 --> 36:03.634
As soon I saw you, I knew there
was no need for a DNA test.

36:05.537 --> 36:07.438
You're my daughter.

36:09.675 --> 36:12.410
I know this is really,
really confusing. Ok?

36:12.444 --> 36:13.878
Believe me, I get it.

36:13.912 --> 36:17.615
But you need to understand that
before I was served those papers,

36:17.649 --> 36:21.552
- I had no idea you even existed.
- No.

36:21.587 --> 36:22.910
My dad, Donald,

36:22.911 --> 36:26.813
he told me that you left after
you found out Mom was pregnant.

36:27.459 --> 36:28.792
No. I never should have left your mom,

36:28.793 --> 36:30.593
that's the worst thing
I've ever done in my life.

36:31.530 --> 36:33.765
But I swear I did not
know she was pregnant.

36:33.799 --> 36:35.566
I loved your mom a lot.

36:41.640 --> 36:43.441
I brought you this.

36:45.511 --> 36:47.478
Just read it when you have the time.

36:47.513 --> 36:50.615
Are you going to sign the papers?

36:50.649 --> 36:52.850
As soon as my attorneys say it's ok.

36:52.885 --> 36:55.686
I gotta get back to work.

37:01.794 --> 37:05.863
Hey, just wanted to let you know we
found a body near that halfway house.

37:05.898 --> 37:08.566
No ID yet, but it could be
the woman you're looking for.

37:12.871 --> 37:16.441
[humming]

37:51.743 --> 37:54.612
[rock music plays on computer]

38:09.428 --> 38:10.795
- [playing piano with music]
- ♪ I ♪

38:10.829 --> 38:14.832
♪ I don't wanna waste your time ♪

38:14.867 --> 38:18.769
♪ And I don't need you wasting mine ♪

38:18.804 --> 38:22.840
♪ So leave it on the front lawn ♪

38:25.444 --> 38:27.478
- ♪ Drive ♪
- Hey.

38:27.513 --> 38:29.814
- Hey.
- That was pretty cool.

38:29.848 --> 38:31.883
Oh, thanks. It's... it's nothing.

38:31.917 --> 38:33.918
Oh, come on. It's not just nothing.

38:33.952 --> 38:36.821
Um...

38:36.855 --> 38:40.491
So your mom and I've been talking.

38:40.526 --> 38:44.729
And I know you know that we're not
exactly on the same page on this.

38:44.763 --> 38:47.532
But I don't know what to do, B.

38:47.566 --> 38:50.468
If we let you have the surgery
and it causes more damage,

38:50.502 --> 38:51.702
are you gonna blame us when you're older

38:51.737 --> 38:55.373
because we let you make this
decision when you were only 16?

38:55.407 --> 38:58.576
And if we don't, are we getting
in the way of your dream?

38:58.610 --> 39:01.579
- I would never blame you.
- But I would.

39:01.613 --> 39:05.750
I'm your mom, B, ok? I'm
supposed to protect you.

39:05.784 --> 39:08.586
And, uh...

39:08.620 --> 39:13.491
... that's a lot harder...
[laughs] these days.

39:15.794 --> 39:18.529
I don't know what the right choice is.

39:20.632 --> 39:24.569
